HANTAVIRUS UPDATE 2011 - AMERICAS (19): CHILE (MAULE)
******************************************************

A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Tue 5 Apr 2011
Source: Radio Bio-Bio [in Spanish, trans. Mod.TY, edited]
http://www.biobiochile.cl/2011/04/05/un-nuevo-caso-de-hanta-virus-fue-confirmado-en-la-region-del-maule.shtml


The Public Health Institute confirmed a new case of [a] hantavirus
[infection] in the San Javier area in the Maule region. The case is a
54 year old agricultural worker who died this past 1 Apr [2011] and
who, today [5 Apr 2011] was confirmed as a positive hantavirus
[infection] case by the Public Health Institute.

It is worth mentioning that 3 hantavirus [infection] cases have been
registered this year [2011] in the Maule region, of which 2 have been
mild and one with a fatal outcome.

--
Communicated by:
HealthMap Alerts via ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[This is the 3rd case of a hantavirus infection in the Maule region
this year (2011). The previous (2nd) case was a 37 year old
agricultural worker who was reported recovering from his infection on
19 Mar 2011 (see ProMED-mail archive number 20110323.0907)

Although not specified, the specific hantavirus involved with this
confirmed case of hantavirus infection in Chile most likely is Andes
virus. Its rodent host is the long-tailed pygmy rice rat(_Oligoryzomys
longicaudatus_), the sigmodontine rodent host of Andes hantavirus --
see image at http://www.bios.niu.edu/frayjorge/rod6.jpg.

The regions of Chile can be seen on the map at
http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Administrative_divisions_of_Chile. A
HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map showing the location of Maule
region in central Chile can be accessed at
http://healthmap.org/r/0C3A. - Mod.TY]
